definitions: an outcrop of rocks that is entirely surrounded by older rocks
a person, thing, or part situated away from a main or related body
a person who lives away from his or her place of work, duty, etc
a point in a sample widely separated from the main cluster of points in the sample
a person or thing that lies outside
a person residing outside the place of his or her business, duty, etc
a part of a formation left detached through the removal of surrounding parts by erosion
